              "settings": {
                "editor": "<style>@media(max-width:600px){#ab-desc-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr!important}#ab-desc-grid>div:first-child{display:none!important}}</style><div style='display:grid;grid-template-columns:60px 1fr;' id='ab-desc-grid' id='ab-desc-grid' style='display:grid;grid-template-columns:60px 1fr;gap:32px;max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;font-family:Inter,Playfair Display,sans-serif;'><div style='display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:8px;'><div style='width:1px;flex:1;background:linear-gradient(180deg,#008080,rgba(0,128,128,.1));'></div><div style='width:8px;height:8px;border:2px solid #008080;border-radius:50%;'></div><div style='width:1px;flex:1;background:linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(0,128,128,.1),transparent);'></div></div><div><p style='font-size:16px;color:#6b7a8d;line-height:2;margin-bottom:18px;'>Strategic Solutions for Research and Consulting (SSRC) is a Damascus-based research and consulting firm dedicated to unlocking knowledge, data, and insights that drive progress and informed decision-making. With extensive experience in public opinion research and analysis, SSRC rigorously measures, analyzes, and interprets social, political, and consumer trends across Syria � with nationwide access from Abukamal to Tartus and Aleppo to As-Suwayda.</p><p style='font-size:16px;color:#6b7a8d;line-height:2;margin-bottom:0;'>SSRC's work spans a wide range of sectors vital to national recovery and sustainable growth, including business management, education, tourism, governance, social affairs, and community development.</p></div></div>"
